  h1.splash.docs-page-header Tables

  section.docs-section#defaults
    h1.docs-h1 Defaults
    p.
      Tables have a light border, with ample padding for text to be easily readable and a
      bold-but-understated table header. To apply the aegis style to any table add a
      <code>.table</code> class to it.

    .example.docs-eg
      table.table.docs-eg-object
        thead
          tr
            th Team
            th Played
            th Points
        tbody
          tr
            td Man Utd
            td 33
            td 81
          tr
            td Man City
            td 33
            td 68
          tr
            td Chelsea
            td 32
            td 61
          tr
            td Arsenal
            td 33
            td 60
          tr
            td Tottenham
            td 32
            td 58
      pre.docs-eg-code.
        &lt;table class='table'&gt;
          &lt;thead&gt;...&lt;/thead&gt;
          &lt;tbody&gt;...&lt;/tbody&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;

  section.docs-section#classes
    h1.docs-h1 Classes
    p.
      Along with the default styling, there are also several classes which can be used
      to give the tables more styles. Some of them change the complete style
      (<strong>style classes</strong>) and some adjust the spacing of the cells
      (<strong>spatial classes</strong>)



