  section.docs-section#cells
    h1.docs-h1 Cells
    p.
      Along with the specific widths for tables, you also get power to control the
      widths of individual columns, so that you can fine-tune the table look.
      Apply the classes on the cells of the <strong>first row</strong> of the table,
      and the corresponding column will resized. The classes are of the form
      <code>.cells-X</code>, where <code>X</code> ranges from
      <code>1 (10% width)</code> to <code>9 (90% width)</code>.

    .example.docs-eg
      table.table.docs-eg-object
        thead
          tr
            th.cell-8 Testing
            th.cell-3 Cells
        tbody
          tr
            td 5
            td Cells are meant to be adjustable
          tr
            td 2
            td And it will be better if they be resizable according to you
          tr
            td 10
            td rather than depending on your browser
      pre.docs-eg-code.
        &lt;table class="table"&gt;
          &lt;thead&gt;
            &lt;tr&gt;
              &lt;th class="cell-8"&gt;Testing&lt;/th&gt;
              &lt;th class="cell-2"&gt;Cells&lt;/th&gt;
            &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;/thead&gt;
          &lt;tbody&gt;
            ...
          &lt;/tbody&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
